{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "web:job.15",
    "translationId": "web",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 15,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 15",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 15 in World English Bible."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.1",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:1",
      "text": "Then Eliphaz the Temanite answered,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.2",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:2",
      "text": "“Should a wise man answer with vain knowledge, and fill himself with the east wind?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.3",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:3",
      "text": "Should he reason with unprofitable talk, or with speeches with which he can do no good?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.4",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:4",
      "text": "Yes, you do away with fear, and hinder devotion before God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.5",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:5",
      "text": "For your iniquity teaches your mouth, and you choose the language of the crafty.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.6",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:6",
      "text": "Your own mouth condemns you, and not I. Yes, your own lips testify against you.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.7",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:7",
      "text": "“Are you the first man who was born? Or were you brought out before the hills?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.8",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:8",
      "text": "Have you heard the secret counsel of God? Do you limit wisdom to yourself?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.9",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:9",
      "text": "What do you know that we don’t know? What do you understand which is not in us?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.10",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:10",
      "text": "With us are both the gray-headed and the very aged men, much older than your father.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.11",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:11",
      "text": "Are the consolations of God too small for you, even the word that is gentle toward you?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.12",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:12",
      "text": "Why does your heart carry you away? Why do your eyes flash,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.13",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:13",
      "text": "that you turn your spirit against God, and let such words go out of your mouth?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.14",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:14",
      "text": "What is man, that he should be clean? What is he who is born of a woman, that he should be righteous?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.15",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:15",
      "text": "Behold, he puts no trust in his holy ones. Yes, the heavens are not clean in his sight;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.16",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:16",
      "text": "how much less one who is abominable and corrupt, a man who drinks iniquity like water!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.17",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:17",
      "text": "“I will show you, listen to me; that which I have seen I will declare",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.18",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:18",
      "text": "(which wise men have told by their fathers, and have not hidden it;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.19",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:19",
      "text": "to whom alone the land was given, and no stranger passed among them):",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.20",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:20",
      "text": "the wicked man writhes in pain all his days, even the number of years that are laid up for the oppressor.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.21",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:21",
      "text": "A sound of terrors is in his ears. In prosperity the destroyer will come on him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.22",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:22",
      "text": "He doesn’t believe that he will return out of darkness. He is waited for by the sword.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.23",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:23",
      "text": "He wanders abroad for bread, saying, ‘Where is it?’ He knows that the day of darkness is ready at his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.24",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:24",
      "text": "Distress and anguish make him afraid. They prevail against him, as a king ready to the battle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.25",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:25",
      "text": "Because he has stretched out his hand against God, and behaves himself proudly against the Almighty,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.26",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 26,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:26",
      "text": "he runs at him with a stiff neck, with the thick shields of his bucklers,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.27",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 27,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:27",
      "text": "because he has covered his face with his fatness, and gathered fat on his thighs.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.28",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 28,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:28",
      "text": "He has lived in desolate cities, in houses which no one inhabited, which were ready to become heaps.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.29",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 29,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:29",
      "text": "He will not be rich, neither will his substance continue, neither will their possessions be extended on the earth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.30",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 30,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:30",
      "text": "He will not depart out of darkness. The flame will dry up his branches. He will go away by the breath of God’s mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.31",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 31,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:31",
      "text": "Let him not trust in emptiness, deceiving himself, for emptiness will be his reward.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.32",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 32,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:32",
      "text": "It will be accomplished before his time. His branch will not be green.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.33",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 33,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:33",
      "text": "He will shake off his unripe grape as the vine, and will cast off his flower as the olive tree.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.34",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 34,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:34",
      "text": "For the company of the godless will be barren, and fire will consume the tents of bribery.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "web:job.15.35",
      "translationId": "web",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 15,
      "verseNumber": 35,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 15:35",
      "text": "They conceive mischief and produce iniquity. Their heart prepares deceit.”",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
